## Secure SSH Configuration

Weak SSH Configuration?
Outdated cryptographic algorithms expose servers to modern brute-force and cryptanalysis attacks. We use `ssh-audit` to harden our SSH server configurations.

### Verification Step
Run the audit tool against the target server:
```bash
python3 -m pip install ssh-audit
ssh-audit <target-ip>

If the report flags any deprecated algorithms, weak ciphers (e.g., CBC modes), or weak MACs:

Open the SSH daemon configuration file (usually /etc/ssh/sshd_config).

Explicitly define secure KexAlgorithms, Ciphers, and MACs (refer to the recommended output provided at the bottom of the ssh-audit report).

Restart the SSH service: sudo systemctl restart ssh

Re-run ssh-audit until the report returns clean (green) with no warnings or errors.
